description_html:
This gallery contains a generic image of each of the Sixteen Types.

They are in alphabetical order, and the preference ratio used in all images is 58% to 42%. This makes all the images quite colorful, while solidly expressing the personality's preferences.

Although we should all be proud of who we are, I strongly believe that we should never think for a second that one type is 'better' than another!

image_list.title: ENFJ
image_list.subject_line: Image of an ENFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Red lines in this image represent the ENFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their warmth causes them to seek harmonious relationships and social connections, making ENFJs outgoing, polite, friendly, charming, and loyal.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENFJ personality types.

image_list.title: ENFP
image_list.subject_line: Image of an ENFP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Blue lines in this image represent the ENFP's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition.  Their openness causes them to explore alternatives and find hidden possibilities.  ENFPs are perceptive, charismatic, versatile, clever, and are enthusiastic about making things happen.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENFP is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENFP personality types.

image_list.title: ENTJ
image_list.subject_line: Image of an ENTJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Green lines in this image represent the ENTJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Thinking.  Their ability to reason logically enables them to organize their environment and schedule events to efficiently produce results.  ENTJs seek logical explanations, are analytical and decisive, work well in organizations, and can make excellent leaders.

image_list.title: INFJ
image_list.subject_line: Image of an INFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Blue lines in this image represent the INFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their inner vision makes them insightful, ingenious, and individualistic.  INFJs are driven, inspired, and determined to overcome difficulties and find new paths in any field they choose.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Red lines represent the INFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their desire for harmonious relationships makes them polite and open to what others want.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an INFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of INFJ personality types.

image_list.title: INFP
image_list.subject_line: Image of an INFP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Red lines in this image represent the INFP's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted Feeling.  Their deep passion for inner harmony rarely surfaces, and an inner morality takes precedence, so the opinions of others matter little.  INFPs are idealistic, authentic and faithful, and have a strong sense of duty.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Red lines represent the INFP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition.  Their quest for insight makes them open to others' thoughts, experiences, ideas, and feelings.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an INFP is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of INFP personality types.

image_list.title: INTP
image_list.subject_line: Image of an INTP using fixed percentages.

Their impersonal analysis of concepts and facts can make them seem shy and aloof.  INTPs are quiet, curious, adaptable, perceptive, and interested in finding underlying principles.

image_list.title: ISFJ
image_list.subject_line: Image of an ISFJ using fixed percentages.

Their practical perceptions and deeply stored impressions make them protective of all things they find familiar.  ISFJs are systematic, responsible, hard-working, and easily adapt to routine.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Red lines represent the ISFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their desire for harmonious relationships makes them polite and open to what others want.
